  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Russia is responsible for the current crisis in Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "President of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelenskiy said while addressing the Asian Leadership Summit in Seoul that Russia is responsible for the current crisis in Sri Lanka.",
        "Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said that not only in Sri Lanka but also in many parts of the world, unrest has arisen due to food and fuel shortages and rising prices, and Russia's blocking of the Ukrainian supply chain has been one of the reasons for rising prices and shortages. He added that no one knows how the unrest caused by skyrocketing fuel and food prices will end.",
        "President Zelensky mentioned that Russia's agenda has benefited by blocking the supply chain."
      ],
